  <head>
    <title>Documentation</title>
    <abstract>
      <para>There are three different Swarm documentation `books',
        each of which can be delivered in html, PostScript, dvi or rtf
        format: <citetitle>Overview to Swarm</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Getting Started with Swarm</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Reference Guide for Swarm</citetitle> (available for the
        Objective C or Java interface).  In addition, the SGML source
        which generates the distributions described above, is also
        available as a package.</para>
    </abstract>
  </head>
  
  <tip>
    <para> See our <ulink url="swarmdocs/refbook/swarm.compatibility.sgml.preface.html">
     <citetitle>Porting Notes</citetitle></ulink> to assist you in
     upgrading your existing applications.</para>
  </tip>
